events.name: New York Knicks at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 27 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers matched the second-most wins in franchise history, defeating the New York Knicks 124-105 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 27 points as Cleveland rallies past New York for 61st victory

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 22 points and 10 assists, Aaron Nesmith scored 16 points and Pascal Siakam added 15 on his 31st birthday, leading the Indiana Pacers to a 119-105 victory over the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Haliburton scores 22 points to help send playoff-bound Pacers past Hornets 119-105

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole scored 23 points and the Washington Wizards beat the Sacramento Kings 116-111 Wednesday night to split the season series between the teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Poole and the Wizards pull off rare win with victory over the Kings

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro had 25 points and nine assists and the Miami Heat extended their season-best winning streak to six games with a 124-103 victory over the Boston Celtics on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat extend winning streak to 6 games and snap Celtics' 9-game streak with 124-103 victory

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 22 points, Dillon Brooks added 21 and the Houston Rockets beat the Utah Jazz 143-105 on Wednesday night for their 50th win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 22 points to lead Rockets to 50th win of the season

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis’ driving floater with 3.4 seconds left capped his 34-point night, his highest scoring game with Dallas, in the Mavericks' 120-118 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis overcomes eye injury to lead the Mavericks past the Hawks, 120-118

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes scored 20 points to lead six San Antonio players in double figures and the Spurs beat the short-handed Denver Nuggets 113-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes and Paul lead Spurs past the short-handed Nuggets 113-106

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 33 points, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the short-handed Detroit Pistons 119-103 on Wednesday night for their 11th straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 33 as Thunder top Pistons 119-103 for 11th straight win

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 28 points and James Harden had 21 points and 10 assists to lead the Los Angeles Clippers to a 114-98 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard scores 28 points to lead the Clippers past the Pelicans 114-98
